Class CloudWorkloadRequest

java.lang.Object
com.interzoid.sdk.model.InterzoidRequest
com.interzoid.sdk.model.CloudWorkloadRequest
public class CloudWorkloadRequest extends InterzoidRequest
The CloudWorkloadRequest class is used to run cloud database workload requests against your cloud connected database.

  • Constructor Details

    • CloudWorkloadRequest

      public CloudWorkloadRequest(String apikey, Process process, Source source, Category category, String connectionString, String sourceTableName, String matchColumn, String referenceColumn, boolean json, boolean html)
      Creates a new CloudWorkloadRequest. This constructor is preferred when returning a match report (Process.MATCH_REPORT) as JSON, HTML, or text. Set both the json and html flags to false to return the match report as text.
      Parameters:
      apikey - The API key to be used for the request.
      process - The process to run
      source - The source used for the match report.
      category - The category used for generating the match keys.
      connectionString - The connection string used for the match report.
      sourceTableName - The table used for the match report.
      matchColumn - The column used for matching.
      referenceColumn - An optional reference column used in the report. Set to null if not used.
      json - Return match report as JSON.
      html - Return match report as HTML

    • CloudWorkloadRequest

      public CloudWorkloadRequest(String apikey, Process process, Source source, Category category, String connectionString, String sourceTableName, String matchColumn, String referenceColumn, String newTableName)
      This constructor is preferred when writing match results to a new table, generating SQL insert statements, or returning match keys only. (Process.CREATE_TABLE, Process.KEYS_ONLY, or Process.GEN_SQL)
      Parameters:
      apikey - The API key to be used for the request.
      process - The process to run
      source - The source used for the match report.
      category - The category used for generating the match keys.
      connectionString - The connection string used for the match report.
      sourceTableName - The table used for the match report.
      matchColumn - The column used for matching.
      referenceColumn - An optional reference column used in the report.
      newTableName - A new table to store the match results. This is required if the process is CREATE_TABLE.
